{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_017bWjhi12d969ywpxZf2APw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LkD94p4M6TMw7L8g3fSPen","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The request sent to the external API always includes the complete list of valid taxonomy labels.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This tests a module boundary: whether the classification module correctly formats and sends the full taxonomy list to the external API. To catch a real failure (module forgets taxonomy in request payload), we must mock the API and inspect what the module actually sent. A unit test of a single function cannot verify request formatting to an external service.","test_description":"Mock the external API to capture request payloads. Call classify(document) and verify the captured request includes the complete taxonomy list (e.g., in a labels or choices field). Assert the taxonomy matches the module's configured labels exactly.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"The test must mock the external API to inspect request arguments—this requires Integration level.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.9,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When the API returns a label that is not in the taxonomy, the module returns 'unknown' instead of forwarding the unexpected value to the caller.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This tests defensive validation at the module boundary. The real failure is: module forwards an invalid label from the API without validation. To expose this, we must mock the API to return out-of-taxonomy values and verify the module substitutes 'unknown'. This is a module-level integration test, not a unit test of isolated validation logic.","test_description":"Mock the external API to return invalid labels (not in the configured taxonomy). Call classify(document). Verify the module returns 'unknown' rather than the invalid label. Test with multiple invalid values to ensure consistent error handling.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"The test mocks the API to return invalid labels and verifies the module's response—this is inherently Integration level.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The classification result for the same document is the same across repeated calls.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This tests caching behavior at the module boundary. The real failure is: the module calls the API twice for the same document (cache miss) or returns different results. To expose this, we must mock the API to track call counts and verify the module caches results. Testing cache behavior requires observing the module's interaction with its external dependency, which is Integration level.","test_description":"Mock the external API to track call invocations. Call classify(same_document) twice. Verify: (1) the returned result is identical both times, (2) the API was invoked only once (proving cache hit). Vary document content to confirm cache key is content-based, not timing-based.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"The test requires mocking the API to verify call counts and caching—this is Integration level.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.85,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The number of tokens consumed for a typical document stays within the configured per-call budget.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This tests cost control at the module boundary. The real failure is: the module sends documents exceeding the token budget, or fails to enforce the budget constraint. To expose this, we must mock the API to return token consumption counts and test the module's budget enforcement with documents of various sizes. This requires mocking the external dependency and testing the module's request/response handling, which is Integration level.","test_description":"Mock the external API to return token consumption in the response payload. Configure the module with a per-call token budget. Call classify() with documents of varying sizes (small, medium, large). Verify: (1) documents fitting the budget are accepted and API is called, (2) documents exceeding budget are either truncated before sending or rejected with clear messaging, (3) the token count in the API response never exceeds the configured budget.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"The test mocks the API to return token counts and tests budget enforcement logic with realistic inputs—this requires Integration level.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the API signals that the request rate is too high, the module waits and retries rather than returning an error to the caller.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This tests error handling and retry logic at the module boundary. The real failure is: the module returns a rate-limit error to the caller instead of retrying transparently. To expose this, we must mock the API to return a rate-limit error on the first call and success on the second, and mock the sleep/wait function to avoid real delays. Testing retry logic with a mocked external dependency is Integration level.","test_description":"Mock the external API to return a rate-limit error (429 or equivalent) on the first invocation and a successful response on the second. Mock the sleep/wait function to avoid actual delays. Call classify(document). Verify: (1) the rate-limit error is not returned to the caller, (2) the module retries after waiting, (3) the final result is the successful classification from the retry, (4) the caller experiences no error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"The test requires mocking both the API (to return rate-limit error) and the sleep function (to avoid delays)—this is inherently Integration level.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.9,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12415,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":12415},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"14a391fb-9d7b-4c25-936f-2f26510ccf32","uuid":"6292b2a8-0574-4c55-a06b-eb60c0da58fe"}
